{
  "name": "sequence_detector",
  "description": "Fires when A precedes B within ~300 tick window. A triggers bistable CH ring (a=0,c=-65,d=0) and schedules FS kill at delay=300. FS has self-excitation (w=15, d=2) creating burst that kills CH ring (w=-30). Memory biases coincidence RS weakly (w=1 per CH, ~1 mA/tick average, below rheobase alone). B input (w=5) also below threshold alone. Together: ~6 mA + tonic 2.5 = ~8.5 -> coincidence fires. A alone: 1+2.5=3.5 -> doesn't fire. B alone: 5+2.5=7.5 -> doesn't fire. Both: fires. After 300 ticks, memory auto-kills. Tested: correct order fires, wrong order silent, either alone silent, past-window silent.",
